product: Assigned by Lahey's list of beta-lactamases no accessions or other information available
Assigned by Lahey's list of beta-lactamases no accessions or other information available
ceoB is a cytoplasmic membrane component of the CeoAB-OpcM efflux pump
qacA is a subunit of the qac multidrug efflux pump
MgrA also known as NorR is a regulator for norA norB and tet38. It is a positive regulator for norA expression but is a direct repressor for norB and an indirect repressor of tet38.

MFS transporters are secondary active transporters with single-polypeptide chains containing 400-600 amino acids that transport small solutes across the membrane by using electrochemical gradients. LmrS has 14 transmembrane helices and when expressed in E. coli is capable of extruding a variety of antibiotics inclinding linezolid trimethoprim florfenicol chlorampheniocol erythromycin streptomycin kanamycin and fusidic acid
ArlR is a response regulator that binds to the norA promoter to activate expression. ArlR must first be phosphorylated by ArlS.
ArlS is a protein histidine kinase that phosphorylates ArlR a promoter for norA expression.
MepR is an upstream repressor of MepA in Staphylococcus aureus. It is part of the mepRAB operon.

MepA is an efflux protein regulated by MepR and part of the MepRAB cluster. Its presence in Staphylococcus aureus led to multidrug resistance while it has also been shown to decrease tigecycline susceptibility.

NorA gene cloned from Staphylococcus aureus conferred relatively high resistance to hydrophilic quinolones such as norfloxacin enoxacin ofloxacin and ciprofloxacin in S. aureus and Escherichia coli. Had low or no resistance at all to hydrophobic ones such as nalidixic acid oxolinic acid and sparfloxacin in S. aureus and Escherichia coli.
MgrA also known as NorR is a regulator for norA norB and tet38. It is a positive regulator for norA expression but is a direct repressor for norB and an indirect repressor of tet38.
Tet38 is a tetracycline efflux pump found in the Gram-positive Staphylococcus aureus. It is regulated by mgrA which also regulates NorB.

kdpE is a transcriptional activator that is part of the two-component system KdpD/KdpE that is studied for its regulatory role in potassium transport and has been identified as an adaptive regulator involved in the virulence and intracellular survival of pathogenic bacteria. kdpE regulates a range of virulence loci through direct promoter binding.

PmrF is required for the synthesis and transfer of 4-amino-4-deoxy-L-arabinose (Ara4N) to Lipid A which allows gram-negative bacteria to resist the antimicrobial activity of cationic antimicrobial peptides and antibiotics such as polymyxin. pmrF corresponds to 1 locus in Pseudomonas aeruginosa PAO1 and 1 locus in Pseudomonas aeruginosa LESB58.

The mphB gene encodes for MPH(2')-II. This enzymes phosphorylates 14-membered and 16-membered macrolides.  It phosphorylates macrolides in GTP- dependent manner at 2'-OH hydroxyl of desosamine sugar of macrolides.
AcrD is an aminoglycoside efflux pump expressed in E. coli. Its expression can be induced by indole and is regulated by baeRS and cpxAR.
An ampC-like beta-lactamase identified from Escherichia coli.
EvgS is a sensor protein that phosphorylates the regulatory protein EvgA. evgS corresponds to 1 locus in Pseudomonas aeruginosa PAO1 and 1 locus in Pseudomonas aeruginosa LESB58.

EvgA when phosphorylated is a positive regulator for efflux protein complexes emrKY and mdtEF. While usually phosphorylated in a EvgS dependent manner it can be phosphorylated in the absence of EvgS when overexpressed.
emrK is a membrane fusion protein that is a homolog of EmrA. Together with the inner membrane transporter EmrY and the outer membrane channel TolC it mediates multidrug efflux.
emrY is a multidrug transport that moves substrates across the inner membrane of the Gram-negative E. coli. It is a homolog of emrB.
CpxA is a membrane-localized sensor kinase that is activated by envelope stress. It starts a kinase cascade that activates CpxR which promotes efflux complex expression.
emrB is a translocase in the emrB -TolC efflux protein in E. coli. It recognizes substrates including carbonyl cyanide m-chlorophenylhydrazone (CCCP) nalidixic acid and thioloactomycin.
EmrA is a membrane fusion protein providing an efflux pathway with EmrB and TolC between the inner and outer membranes of E. coli a Gram-negative bacterium.
EmrR is a negative regulator for the EmrAB-TolC multidrug efflux pump in E. coli. Mutations lead to EmrAB-TolC overexpression.
In the presence of antibiotic stress E. coli overexpresses the global activator protein MarA which besides inducing MDR efflux pump AcrAB also down- regulates synthesis of the porin OmpF.

The MdtG protein also named YceE appears to be a member of the major facilitator superfamily of transporters and it has been reported when overexpressed to increase fosfomycin and deoxycholate resistances. mdtG is a member of the marA-soxS-rob regulon.
Multidrug resistance protein MdtH

YojI mediates resistance to the peptide antibiotic microcin J25 when it is expressed from a multicopy vector. YojI is capable of pumping out microcin molecules.  The outer membrane protein TolC in addition to YojI is required for export of microcin J25 out of the cell. Microcin J25 is thus the first known substrate for YojI.
BaeR is a response regulator that promotes the expression of MdtABC and AcrD efflux complexes.
BaeS is a sensor kinase in the BaeSR regulatory system. While it phosphorylates BaeR to increase its activity BaeS is not necessary for overexpressed BaeR to confer resistance.

MdtC is a transporter that forms a heteromultimer complex with MdtB to form a multidrug transporter. MdtBC is part of the MdtABC-TolC efflux complex. In the absence of MdtB MdtC can form a homomultimer complex that results in a functioning efflux complex with a narrower drug specificity. mdtC corresponds to 3 loci in Pseudomonas aeruginosa PAO1 (gene name: muxC/muxB) and 3 loci in Pseudomonas aeruginosa LESB58.
MdtB is a transporter that forms a heteromultimer complex with MdtC to form a multidrug transporter. MdtBC is part of the MdtABC-TolC efflux complex.
MdtA is the membrane fusion protein of the multidrug efflux complex mdtABC.

PmrE is required for the synthesis and transfer of 4-amino-4-deoxy-L-arabinose (Ara4N) to Lipid A which allows gram-negative bacteria to resist the antimicrobial activity of cationic antimicrobial peptides and antibiotics such as polymyxin

TolC is a protein subunit of many multidrug efflux complexes in Gram negative bacteria. It is an outer membrane efflux protein and is constitutively open. Regulation of efflux activity is often at its periplasmic entrance by other components of the efflux complex.
The bacA gene product (BacA) recycles undecaprenyl pyrophosphate during cell wall biosynthesis which confers resistance to bacitracin.
AcrS is a repressor of the AcrAB efflux complex and is associated with the expression of AcrEF. AcrS is believed to regulate a switch between AcrAB and AcrEF efflux.
AcrE is a membrane fusion protein similar to AcrA.
AcrF is a inner membrane transporter similar to AcrB.
AcrA is a subunit of the AcrAB-TolC multidrug efflux system that in E. coli.

Protein subunit of AcrA-AcrB-TolC multidrug efflux complex. AcrB functions as a herterotrimer which forms the inner membrane component and is primarily responsible for substrate recognition and energy transduction by acting as a drug/proton antiporter.
AmpH is a class C ampC-like beta-lactamase and penicillin-binding protein identified in Escherichia coli.
Multidrug efflux pump in E. coli. This multidrug efflux system was originally identified as the Cmr/CmlA chloramphenicol exporter.

MsbA is a multidrug resistance transporter homolog from E. coli and belongs to a superfamily of transporters that contain an adenosine triphosphate (ATP) binding cassette (ABC) which is also called a nucleotide-binding domain (NBD). MsbA is a member of the MDR-ABC transporter group by sequence homology. MsbA transports lipid A a major component of the bacterial outer cell membrane and is the only bacterial ABC transporter that is essential for cell viability.
Tet(B) is a tetracycline efflux protein expressed in many Gram-negative bacteria. It confers resistance to tetracycline doxycycline and minocycline but not tigecycline.
Sul2 is a sulfonamide resistant dihydropteroate synthase of Gram-negative bacteria usually found on small plasmids.

H-NS is a histone-like protein involved in global gene regulation in Gram-negative bacteria. It is a repressor of the membrane fusion protein genes acrE mdtE and emrK as well as nearby genes of many RND-type multidrug exporters.
GadX is an AraC-family regulator that promotes mdtEF expression to confer multidrug resistance.

GadW is an AraC-family regulator that promotes mdtEF expression to confer multidrug resistance. GadW inhibits GadX-dependent activation. GadW clearly represses gadX and in situations where GadX is missing activates gadA and gadBC.
MdtF is the multidrug inner membrane transporter for the MdtEF-TolC efflux complex.
MdtE is the membrane fusion protein of the MdtEF multidrug efflux complex. It shares 70% sequence similarity with AcrA.
CRP is a global regulator that represses MdtEF multidrug efflux pump expression.
TEM-1 is a broad-spectrum beta-lactamase found in many Gram-negative bacteria. Confers resistance to penicillins and first generation cephalosphorins.
Multidrug resistance protein MdtM
A class C ampC beta-lactamase (cephalosporinase) enzyme described in Escherichia coli shown clinically to confer resistance to penicillin-like and cephalosporin-class antibiotics.

PmrC mediates the modification of Lipid A by the addition of 4-amino-4-deoxy-L-arabinose (L-Ara4N) and phosphoethanolamine resulting in a less negative cell membrane and decreased binding of polymyxin B.
Multidrug resistance efflux pump. Could be involved in resistance to puromycin acriflavine and tetraphenylarsonium chloride.
Multidrug resistance efflux pump. Could be involved in resistance to puromycin acriflavine and tetraphenylarsonium chloride
Multidrug resistance efflux pump. Could be involved in resistance to puromycin acriflavine and tetraphenylarsonium chloride

Klebsiella pneumoniae outer membrane porin protein. Is preferentially detected in porin-deficient strains. Functional characterization of this new porin revealed a narrower pore than those of porins OmpK35 and OmpK36 which did not allow penetration by certain beta-lactams. Also when a resistant strain expresses porin OmpK37 is less susceptible to cefotaxime and cefoxitin than when it is expressing either OmpK36 or OmpK35.

MsbA is a multidrug resistance transporter homolog from E. coli and belongs to a superfamily of transporters that contain an adenosine triphosphate (ATP) binding cassette (ABC) which is also called a nucleotide-binding domain (NBD). MsbA is a member of the MDR-ABC transporter group by sequence homology. MsbA transports lipid A a major component of the bacterial outer cell membrane and is the only bacterial ABC transporter that is essential for cell viability.
RND efflux pump conferring resistance to fluoroquinolone
RND efflux pump conferring resistance to fluoroquinolone
EmrR is a negative regulator for the EmrAB-TolC multidrug efflux pump in E. coli. Mutations lead to EmrAB-TolC overexpression.

KpnG consists of ~390 residues and resembles EmrA of E. coli. Disruption of the pump components KpnG-KpnH signficantly decrease resistance to azithromycin ceftazidime ciprofloxacin ertapenem erythromycin gentamicin imipenem ticarcillin norfloxacin polymyxin-B piperacillin spectinomycin tobramycin and streptomycin

KpnH consists of ~511 residues resembles EmrB of E. coli and is probably a translocase in the KpnGH-TolC efflux protein in K. pneumoniae. Disruption of the pump components KpnG-KpnH signficantly decrease resistance to azithromycin ceftazidime ciprofloxacin ertapenem erythromycin gentamicin imipenem ticarcillin norfloxacin polymyxin-B piperacillin spectinomycin tobramycin and streptomycin.
CpxA is a membrane-localized sensor kinase that is activated by envelope stress. It starts a kinase cascade that activates CpxR which promotes efflux complex expression.
Sul2 is a sulfonamide resistant dihydropteroate synthase of Gram-negative bacteria usually found on small plasmids.
APH(3'')-Ib is an aminoglycoside phosphotransferase encoded by plasmids transposons integrative conjugative elements and chromosomes in Enterobacteriaceae and Pseudomonas spp.

APH(6)-Id is an aminoglycoside phosphotransferase encoded by plasmids integrative conjugative elements and chromosomal genomic islands in K. pneumoniae Salmonella spp. E. coli Shigella flexneri Providencia alcalifaciens Pseudomonas spp. V. cholerae Edwardsiella tarda Pasteurella multocida and Aeromonas bestiarum

RamA (resistance antibiotic multiple) is a positive regulator of AcrAB-TolC and leads to high level multidrug resistance in Klebsiella pneumoniae Salmonella enterica and Enterobacter aerugenes increasing the expression of both the mar operon as well as AcrAB. RamA also decreases OmpF expression.
AcrD is an aminoglycoside efflux pump expressed in E. coli. Its expression can be induced by indole and is regulated by baeRS and cpxAR.

Protein subunit of AcrA-AcrB-TolC multidrug efflux complex. AcrB functions as a herterotrimer which forms the inner membrane component and is primarily responsible for substrate recognition and energy transduction by acting as a drug/proton antiporter.
AcrA is a subunit of the AcrAB multidrug efflux system that in K. pneumoniae which is encoded by the acrRAB operon.

KpnE subunit of KpnEF resembles EbrAB from E. coli. Mutation in KpnEF resulted in increased susceptibility to cefepime ceftriaxon colistin erythromycin rifampin tetracycline and streptomycin as well as enhanced sensitivity toward sodium dodecyl sulfate deoxycholate dyes benzalkonium chloride chlorhexidine and triclosan

KpnF subunit of KpnEF resembles EbrAB from E. coli. Mutation in KpnEF resulted in increased susceptibility to cefepime ceftriaxon colistin erythromycin rifampin tetracycline and streptomycin as well as enhanced sensitivity toward sodium dodecyl sulfate deoxycholate dyes benzalkonium chloride chlorhexidine and triclosan.

KPC-2 is a beta-lactamase found in Klebsiella pneumoniae and Pseudomonas aeruginosa.

SAT-2 is a plasmid-mediated streptothricin acetyltransferase which confers resistance to streptothricin a nucleoside antibiotic. Originally described from an E. coli plasmid sequence by Heim et al. 1989.

In the absence of MdtB MdtC can form a homomultimer complex that results in a functioning efflux complex with a narrower drug specificity. mdtC corresponds to 3 loci in Pseudomonas aeruginosa PAO1 (gene name: muxC/muxB) and 3 loci in Pseudomonas aeruginosa LESB58.
MdtB is a transporter that forms a heteromultimer complex with MdtC to form a multidrug transporter. MdtBC is part of the MdtABC-TolC efflux complex.
fosA6 is a plasmid-encoded enzyme that confers resistance to fosfomycin in Escherichia coli by breaking the epoxide ring of the molecule.
CRP is a global regulator that represses MdtEF multidrug efflux pump expression.

floR is a plasmid or chromosome-encoded chloramphenicol exporter that is found in Bordetella bronchiseptica Escherichia coli Klebsiella pneumoniae Salmonella enterica subsp. enterica serovar Typhimurium str. DT104 and Vibrio cholerae

TetG is a tetracycline efflux protein found in Gram-negative bacteria. The encoding gene is found in both chromosomal and plasmid DNA where it is frequently linked to the floR sul1 and cmlA9 genes which encode proteins that can confer florfenicol/chloramphenicol sulfamethoxazole and chloramphenicol resistance respectively.

RmtB is a 16S rRNA methyltransferase that targets mature or nearly mature 30S subunits. It transfers a methyl group from S-adenosyl-L-methionine to N7-G1405 of the 16S rRNA an aminoglycoside binding site.
Erm42 confers MLSb phenotype in Pasteurella multocida

The mphA gene encodes for resistance enzyme MPH(2')-I which preferentially inactivate 14-membered macrolides (e.g.erythromycin telithromycin roxithromycin) over 16-membered macrolides (e.g.tylosin spiramycin). It phosphorylates macrolides at 2'-OH hydroxyl of desosamine sugar of macrolides in a GTP-dependent manner.
AAC(3)-IId is a plasmid-encoded aminoglycoside acetyltransferase in E. coli
catI is a chromosome and transposon-encoded variant of the cat gene found in Escherichia coli and Acinetobacter baumannii
dfrA12 is an integron-encoded dihydrofolate reductase found in Vibrio cholerae
aadA2 is an aminoglycoside nucleotidyltransferase gene encoded by plasmids and integrons in K. pneumoniae Salmonella spp. Corynebacterium glutamicum C. freundii and Aeromonas spp.
CTX-M-14 is a beta-lactamase found in the Enterobacteriaceae family

APH(3')-Ia is a transposon-encoded aminoglycoside phosphotransferase in E. coli and S. enterica. It is identical at the protein sequence to APH(3')-Ic an aminoglycoside phosphotransferase encoded by plasmids transposons and genomic islands in K. pneumoniae A. baumannii S. marcescens Corynebacterium spp. Photobacterium spp. and Citrobacter spp.
TEM-1 is a broad-spectrum beta-lactamase found in many Gram-negative bacteria. Confers resistance to penicillins and first generation cephalosphorins.

AcrA is a subunit of the AcrAB multidrug efflux system that in K. pneumoniae which is encoded by the acrRAB operon.
CTX-M-15 is a beta-lactamase found in the Enterobacteriaceae family
AAC(3)-IIe is a plasmid-encoded aminoglycoside acetyltransferase in E. coli
OXA-1 is a beta-lactamase found in E. coli

AAC(6')-Ib-cr is an aminoglycoside acetyltransferase encoded by plasmids transposons integrons in Enterobacteriaceae. The aac(6')-Ib-cr variant gene can induce resistance against aminoglycoside and fluoroquinolone simultaneously

APH(3')-Ia is a transposon-encoded aminoglycoside phosphotransferase in E. coli and S. enterica. It is identical at the protein sequence to APH(3')-Ic an aminoglycoside phosphotransferase encoded by plasmids transposons and genomic islands in K. pneumoniae A. baumannii S. marcescens Corynebacterium spp. Photobacterium spp. and Citrobacter spp.

CpxR is directly involved in activation of expression of RND efflux pump MexAB-OprM in P. aeruginosa. CpxR is required to enhance mexAB-oprM expression and drug resistance in the absence of repressor MexR.

An enzyme that confers resistance to fosfomycin in Serratia marcescens by breaking the epoxide ring of the molecule. It depends on the cofactors Manganese (II) and Potassium and uses Glutathione (GSH) as the nucleophilic molecule. In Pseudomonas aeruginosa FosA catalyzes the conjugation of glutathione to carbon-1 of fosfomycin rendering it ineffective as an antibacterial drug.
MexA is the membrane fusion protein of the MexAB-OprM multidrug efflux complex.
MexB is the inner membrane multidrug exporter of the efflux complex MexAB-OprM.
OprM is an outer membrane factor protein found in Pseudomonas aeruginosa and Burkholderia vietnamiensis. It is part of the MexAB-OprM MexVW-OprM MexXY-OprM and the AmrAB-OprM complex.
mexM is the membrane fusion protein of the MexMN-OprM multidrug efflux complex.
MexN is the inner membrane transporter of the MexMN-OprM multidrug efflux complex.
mexK is the inner membrane resistance-nodulation-cell division (RND) transporter in the MexJK multidrug efflux protein.
mexJ is the membrane fusion protein of the MexJK multidrug efflux protein.
MexL is a specific repressor of mexJK transcription and autoregulates its own expression.

ArmR a 53-amino-acid antirepressor allosterically inhibits MexR dimer-DNA binding by occupying a hydrophobic binding cavity within the center of the MexR dimer. ArmR up-regulation and MexR-ArmR complex formation have previously been shown to upregulate MexAB-OprM.
PDC-2 is a extended-spectrum beta-lactamase found in Pseudomonas aeruginosa.
APH(3')-IIb is a chromosomal-encoded aminoglycoside phosphotransferase in P. aeruginosa

Transmembrane protein which expels bicyclomycin from the cell leading to bicyclomycin resistance. Identified in Pseudomonas aeruginosa strains responsible for outbreaks in Brazil often appearing with blaSPM-1 another bicyclomycin resistance gene
Histidine protein kinase sensor Lipid A modification gene; part of a two-component system involved in polymyxin resistance that senses high extracellular Fe(2+)
MexX is the membrane fusion protein of the MexXY-OprM multidrug efflux complex.
MexY is the RND-type membrane protein of the efflux complex MexXY-OprM.

SoxR is a redox-sensitive transcriptional activator that induces expression of a small regulon that includes the RND efflux pump-encoding operon mexGHI-opmD. SoxR was shown to be activated by pyocyanin.
MexV is the membrane fusion protein of the MexVW-OprM multidrug efflux complex.
MexW is the RND-type membrane protein of the efflux complex MexVW-OprM.
OprJ is the outer membrane channel component of the MexCD-OprJ multidrug efflux complex.
MexD is the multidrug inner membrane transporter of the MexCD-OprJ complex.
MexC is the membrane fusion protein of the MexCD-OprJ multidrug efflux complex.
OpmD is the outer membrane channel protein of the efflux complex MexGHI-OpmD.
MexI is the inner membrane transporter of the efflux complex MexGHI-OpmD.
MexH is the membrane fusion protein of the efflux complex MexGHI-OpmD.
MexG is a membrane protein required for MexGHI-OpmD efflux activity.
catB7 is a chromosome-encoded variant of the cat gene found in Pseudomonas aeruginosa
Assigned by Lahey's list of beta-lactamases no accessions or other information available
TriA is a membrane protein that is fused to TriB and both are required for the triclosan efflux pump function of TriABC-OpmH in P. aeruginosa.
TriB is a membrane protein that is fused to TriA and both are required for the triclosan efflux pump function of TriABC-OpmH in P. aeruginosa.
TriC is a resistance nodulation cell division (RND) transporter that is a part of TriABC-OpmH a triclosan-specific efflux protein.
OpmH is an outer membrane efflux protein required for triclosan-specific efflux pump function.

EmrE is a small multidrug transporter that functions as a homodimer and that couples the efflux of small polyaromatic cations from the cell with the import of protons down an electrochemical gradient. Confers resistance to tetraphenylphosphonium methyl viologen gentamicin kanamycin and neomycin.
MuxA is a membrane fusion protein component of the efflux pump system MuxABC-OpmB in Pseudomonas aeruginosa.
MuxB is one of the two necessary RND components in the Pseudomonas aeruginosa efflux pump system MuxABC-OpmB.
MuxC is one of the two necessary RND components of the MuxABC-OpmB efflux pumps system in Pseudomonas aeruginosa.
OpmB is an outer membrane efflux protein in Pseudomonas aeruginosa that shows functional cooperation with MuxABC to form the efflux pump system MuxABC-OpmB.
OprN is the outer membrane channel component of the MexEF-OprN multidrug efflux complex.

MexF is the multidrug inner membrane transporter of the MexEF-OprN complex. mexF corresponds to 2 loci in Pseudomonas aeruginosa PAO1 (gene name: mexF/mexB) and 4 loci in Pseudomonas aeruginosa LESB58 (gene name: mexD/mexB).
MexE is the membrane fusion protein of the MexEF-OprN multidrug efflux complex.

PmpM is a multidrug efflux pump belonging to the MATE family of Pseudomonas aeruginosa. PmpM is an H+ drug antiporter and is the first reported case of an H+ coupled efflux pump in the MATE family. PmpM confers resistance to fluoroquinolones fradiomycin benzalkonium chloride chlorhexidine gluconate ethidium bromide tetraphenylphosphonium chloride (TPPCl) and rhodamine 6G.
opmE is an outer membrane factor protein that is part of the multidrug efflux pump MexPQ-OpmE.
MexQ is the inner membrane transporter of the multidrug efflux pump MexPQ-OpmE.
MexP is the membrane fusion protein of the MexPQ-OpmE multidrug efflux complex

BaeS is a sensor kinase in the BaeSR regulatory system. While it phosphorylates BaeR to increase its activity BaeS is not necessary for overexpressed BaeR to confer resistance.

MdtC is a transporter that forms a heteromultimer complex with MdtB to form a multidrug transporter. MdtBC is part of the MdtABC-TolC efflux complex. In the absence of MdtB MdtC can form a homomultimer complex that results in a functioning efflux complex with a narrower drug specificity. mdtC corresponds to 3 loci in Pseudomonas aeruginosa PAO1 (gene name: muxC/muxB) and 3 loci in Pseudomonas aeruginosa LESB58.
MdtB is a transporter that forms a heteromultimer complex with MdtC to form a multidrug transporter. MdtBC is part of the MdtABC-TolC efflux complex.
MdtA is the membrane fusion protein of the multidrug efflux complex mdtABC.
Multidrug resistance efflux pump. Could be involved in resistance to puromycin acriflavine and tetraphenylarsonium chloride
Multidrug resistance efflux pump. Could be involved in resistance to puromycin acriflavine and tetraphenylarsonium chloride
Multidrug resistance efflux pump. Could be involved in resistance to puromycin acriflavine and tetraphenylarsonium chloride.

PmrC mediates the modification of Lipid A by the addition of 4-amino-4-deoxy-L-arabinose (L-Ara4N) and phosphoethanolamine resulting in a less negative cell membrane and decreased binding of polymyxin B.
A class C ampC beta-lactamase (cephalosporinase) enzyme described in Escherichia coli shown clinically to confer resistance to penicillin-like and cephalosporin-class antibiotics.
The bacA gene product (BacA) recycles undecaprenyl pyrophosphate during cell wall biosynthesis which confers resistance to bacitracin.
Multidrug efflux pump in E. coli. This multidrug efflux system was originally identified as the Cmr/CmlA chloramphenicol exporter.

The mphB gene encodes for MPH(2')-II. This enzymes phosphorylates 14-membered and 16-membered macrolides.  It phosphorylates macrolides in GTP- dependent manner at 2'-OH hydroxyl of desosamine sugar of macrolides.
AcrA is a subunit of the AcrAB-TolC multidrug efflux system that in E. coli.

Protein subunit of AcrA-AcrB-TolC multidrug efflux complex. AcrB functions as a herterotrimer which forms the inner membrane component and is primarily responsible for substrate recognition and energy transduction by acting as a drug/proton antiporter.
Multidrug resistance protein MdtM

YojI mediates resistance to the peptide antibiotic microcin J25 when it is expressed from a multicopy vector. YojI is capable of pumping out microcin molecules.  The outer membrane protein TolC in addition to YojI is required for export of microcin J25 out of the cell. Microcin J25 is thus the first known substrate for YojI.

MsbA is a multidrug resistance transporter homolog from E. coli and belongs to a superfamily of transporters that contain an adenosine triphosphate (ATP) binding cassette (ABC) which is also called a nucleotide-binding domain (NBD). MsbA is a member of the MDR-ABC transporter group by sequence homology. MsbA transports lipid A a major component of the bacterial outer cell membrane and is the only bacterial ABC transporter that is essential for cell viability.
In the presence of antibiotic stress E. coli overexpresses the global activator protein MarA which besides inducing MDR efflux pump AcrAB also down- regulates synthesis of the porin OmpF.
An ampC-like beta-lactamase identified from Escherichia coli.
CRP is a global regulator that represses MdtEF multidrug efflux pump expression.

PmrE is required for the synthesis and transfer of 4-amino-4-deoxy-L-arabinose (Ara4N) to Lipid A which allows gram-negative bacteria to resist the antimicrobial activity of cationic antimicrobial peptides and antibiotics such as polymyxin
AmpH is a class C ampC-like beta-lactamase and penicillin-binding protein identified in Escherichia coli.
emrY is a multidrug transport that moves substrates across the inner membrane of the Gram-negative E. coli. It is a homolog of emrB.
emrK is a membrane fusion protein that is a homolog of EmrA. Together with the inner membrane transporter EmrY and the outer membrane channel TolC it mediates multidrug efflux.

EvgA when phosphorylated is a positive regulator for efflux protein complexes emrKY and mdtEF. While usually phosphorylated in a EvgS dependent manner it can be phosphorylated in the absence of EvgS when overexpressed.
EvgS is a sensor protein that phosphorylates the regulatory protein EvgA. evgS corresponds to 1 locus in Pseudomonas aeruginosa PAO1 and 1 locus in Pseudomonas aeruginosa LESB58.
EmrR is a negative regulator for the EmrAB-TolC multidrug efflux pump in E. coli. Mutations lead to EmrAB-TolC overexpression.
EmrA is a membrane fusion protein providing an efflux pathway with EmrB and TolC between the inner and outer membranes of E. coli a Gram-negative bacterium.
emrB is a translocase in the emrB -TolC efflux protein in E. coli. It recognizes substrates including carbonyl cyanide m-chlorophenylhydrazone (CCCP) nalidixic acid and thioloactomycin.

TolC is a protein subunit of many multidrug efflux complexes in Gram negative bacteria. It is an outer membrane efflux protein and is constitutively open. Regulation of efflux activity is often at its periplasmic entrance by other components of the efflux complex.
CpxA is a membrane-localized sensor kinase that is activated by envelope stress. It starts a kinase cascade that activates CpxR which promotes efflux complex expression.
Multidrug resistance protein MdtH

The MdtG protein also named YceE appears to be a member of the major facilitator superfamily of transporters and it has been reported when overexpressed to increase fosfomycin and deoxycholate resistances. mdtG is a member of the marA-soxS-rob regulon.

kdpE is a transcriptional activator that is part of the two-component system KdpD/KdpE that is studied for its regulatory role in potassium transport and has been identified as an adaptive regulator involved in the virulence and intracellular survival of pathogenic bacteria. kdpE regulates a range of virulence loci through direct promoter binding.
GadX is an AraC-family regulator that promotes mdtEF expression to confer multidrug resistance.

GadW is an AraC-family regulator that promotes mdtEF expression to confer multidrug resistance. GadW inhibits GadX-dependent activation. GadW clearly represses gadX and in situations where GadX is missing activates gadA and gadBC.
MdtF is the multidrug inner membrane transporter for the MdtEF-TolC efflux complex.
MdtE is the membrane fusion protein of the MdtEF multidrug efflux complex. It shares 70% sequence similarity with AcrA.

H-NS is a histone-like protein involved in global gene regulation in Gram-negative bacteria. It is a repressor of the membrane fusion protein genes acrE mdtE and emrK as well as nearby genes of many RND-type multidrug exporters.
AcrS is a repressor of the AcrAB efflux complex and is associated with the expression of AcrEF. AcrS is believed to regulate a switch between AcrAB and AcrEF efflux.
AcrE is a membrane fusion protein similar to AcrA.
AcrF is a inner membrane transporter similar to AcrB.
BaeR is a response regulator that promotes the expression of MdtABC and AcrD efflux complexes.

Member of the small MDR (multidrug resistance) family of transporters; in Escherichia coli this protein provides resistance against a number of positively charged compounds including ethidium bromide and erythromycin; proton-dependent secondary transporter which exchanges protons for compound translocation

PmrF is required for the synthesis and transfer of 4-amino-4-deoxy-L-arabinose (Ara4N) to Lipid A which allows gram-negative bacteria to resist the antimicrobial activity of cationic antimicrobial peptides and antibiotics such as polymyxin. pmrF corresponds to 1 locus in Pseudomonas aeruginosa PAO1 and 1 locus in Pseudomonas aeruginosa LESB58.
AcrD is an aminoglycoside efflux pump expressed in E. coli. Its expression can be induced by indole and is regulated by baeRS and cpxAR.
ArlS is a protein histidine kinase that phosphorylates ArlR a promoter for norA expression.
ArlR is a response regulator that binds to the norA promoter to activate expression. ArlR must first be phosphorylated by ArlS.

MFS transporters are secondary active transporters with single-polypeptide chains containing 400-600 amino acids that transport small solutes across the membrane by using electrochemical gradients. LmrS has 14 transmembrane helices and when expressed in E. coli is capable of extruding a variety of antibiotics inclinding linezolid trimethoprim florfenicol chlorampheniocol erythromycin streptomycin kanamycin and fusidic acid
Tet38 is a tetracycline efflux pump found in the Gram-positive Staphylococcus aureus. It is regulated by mgrA which also regulates NorB.
The Bacillus subtilis fosB gene encodes a fosfomycin resistance protein
The blaZ beta-lactamase is found in Bacillus subtilis and Staphylococcus aureus.
MepR is an upstream repressor of MepA in Staphylococcus aureus. It is part of the mepRAB operon.

MepA is an efflux protein regulated by MepR and part of the MepRAB cluster. Its presence in Staphylococcus aureus led to multidrug resistance while it has also been shown to decrease tigecycline susceptibility.
MgrA also known as NorR is a regulator for norA norB and tet38. It is a positive regulator for norA expression but is a direct repressor for norB and an indirect repressor of tet38.

NorA gene cloned from Staphylococcus aureus conferred relatively high resistance to hydrophilic quinolones such as norfloxacin enoxacin ofloxacin and ciprofloxacin in S. aureus and Escherichia coli. Had low or no resistance at all to hydrophobic ones such as nalidixic acid oxolinic acid and sparfloxacin in S. aureus and Escherichia coli.
smeD is the membrane fusion protein of the smeDEF multidrug efflux complex in Stenotrophomonas maltophilia
smeE is the RND protein of the efflux complex smeDEF in Stenotrophomonas maltophilia
smeF is an outer membrane multidrug efflux protein of the smeDEF complex in Stenotrophomonas maltophilia
smeR is the responder component of a two component signal transduction system that includes smeS
smeS is the protein kinase sensor component of a two component signal transduction system that includes smeR
smeA is the membrane fusion protein of the smeABC multidrug efflux complex in Stenotrophomonas maltophilia
smeB is the inner membrane multidrug exporter of the efflux complex smeABC in Stenotrophomonas maltophilia
smeC is an outer membrane multidrug efflux protein of the smeABC complex in Stenotrophomonas maltophilia

L1 is an Ambler class B MBL; subclass B3 originally isolated from Stenotrophomonas maltophilia.  It has activity against a broad range of beta-lactams and is only active with two Zn(II) ions in the active site.
APH(3')-IIc is a chromosomal-encoded aminoglycoside phosphotransferase in S. maltophilia
MgrA also known as NorR is a regulator for norA norB and tet38. It is a positive regulator for norA expression but is a direct repressor for norB and an indirect repressor of tet38.

NorA is a multidrug efflux pump in Staphylococcus aureus that confers resistance to fluoroquinolones and other structurally unrelated antibiotics like acriflavine. It shares 30% similarity with NorA and is a structural homolog of Bmr of Bacillus subtilis. It is regulated by arlRS and mgrA the latter also known as NorR.
The blaZ beta-lactamase is found in Bacillus subtilis and Staphylococcus aureus.
A foreign PBP2a acquired by lateral gene transfer that able to perform peptidoglycan synthesis in the presence of beta-lactams.

ErmB confers the MLSb phenotype. Similar to ErmC expression of ErmB is inducible by erythromycin. The leader peptide causes attenuation of the mRNA and stabilizes the structure preventing further translation. When erythromycin is present it binds the leader peptide causing a change in conformation allowing for the expression of ErmB.

ErmC is a methyltransferase that catalyzes the methylation of A2058 of the 23S ribosomal RNA in two steps. Expression of ErmC is inducible by erythromycin. The leader peptide causes attenuation of the mRNA and stabilizes the structure preventing further translation. When erythromycin is present it binds the leader peptide causing a change in conformation allowing for the expression of ErmC.

CTX-M-15 is a beta-lactamase found in the Enterobacteriaceae family
CRP is a global regulator that represses MdtEF multidrug efflux pump expression.
Sul1 is a sulfonamide resistant dihydropteroate synthase of Gram-negative bacteria. It is linked to other resistance genes of class 1 integrons.
dfrA10 is an integron-encoded dihydrofolate reductase found in Klebsiella pneumoniae

Plasmid or integron-encoded nucleotidylylation of 2-deoxystreptamine aminoglycosides at the hydroxyl group at position 2'' in P. aeruginosa K. pneumoniae Morganella morganii E. coli S. typhimurium C. freundii and A. baumannii
catI is a chromosome and transposon-encoded variant of the cat gene found in Escherichia coli and Acinetobacter baumannii
Tet(B) is a tetracycline efflux protein expressed in many Gram-negative bacteria. It confers resistance to tetracycline doxycycline and minocycline but not tigecycline.

AAC(6')-Ib-cr is an aminoglycoside acetyltransferase encoded by plasmids transposons integrons in Enterobacteriaceae. The aac(6')-Ib-cr variant gene can induce resistance against aminoglycoside and fluoroquinolone simultaneously
OXA-1 is a beta-lactamase found in E. coli
catB3 is a plasmid or chromosome-encoded variant of the cat gene found in Salmonella typhimurium Acinetobacter baumannii and Escherichia coli

APH(3')-Ia is a transposon-encoded aminoglycoside phosphotransferase in E. coli and S. enterica. It is identical at the protein sequence to APH(3')-Ic an aminoglycoside phosphotransferase encoded by plasmids transposons and genomic islands in K. pneumoniae A. baumannii S. marcescens Corynebacterium spp. Photobacterium spp. and Citrobacter spp.
DHA-13 is a beta-lactamase. From the Lahey list of DHA beta-lactamases.
SHV-106 is an extended-spectrum beta-lactamase that has been found in clinical isolates.

Klebsiella pneumoniae outer membrane porin protein. Is preferentially detected in porin-deficient strains. Member of the small MDR (multidrug resistance) family of transporters; in Escherichia coli this protein provides resistance against a number of positively charged compounds including ethidium bromide and erythromycin; proton-dependent secondary transporter which exchanges protons for compound translocation

MsbA is a multidrug resistance transporter homolog from E. coli and belongs to a superfamily of transporters that contain an adenosine triphosphate (ATP) binding cassette (ABC) which is also called a nucleotide-binding domain (NBD). MsbA is a member of the MDR-ABC transporter group by sequence homology. MsbA transports lipid A a major component of the bacterial outer cell membrane and is the only bacterial ABC transporter that is essential for cell viability.
Multidrug efflux pump in E. coli. This multidrug efflux system was originally identified as the Cmr/CmlA chloramphenicol exporter.
KPC-2 is a beta-lactamase found in Klebsiella pneumoniae and Pseudomonas aeruginosa.
EmrR is a negative regulator for the EmrAB-TolC multidrug efflux pump in E. coli. Mutations lead to EmrAB-TolC overexpression.
EmrA is a membrane fusion protein providing an efflux pathway with EmrB and TolC between the inner and outer membranes of E. coli a Gram-negative bacterium.
emrB is a translocase in the emrB -TolC efflux protein in E. coli. It recognizes substrates including carbonyl cyanide m-chlorophenylhydrazone (CCCP) nalidixic acid and thioloactomycin.
MdtE is the membrane fusion protein of the MdtEF multidrug efflux complex. It shares 70% sequence similarity with AcrA.
MdtF is the multidrug inner membrane transporter for the MdtEF-TolC efflux complex.

GadW is an AraC-family regulator that promotes mdtEF expression to confer multidrug resistance. GadW inhibits GadX-dependent activation. GadW clearly represses gadX and in situations where GadX is missing activates gadA and gadBC.
GadX is an AraC-family regulator that promotes mdtEF expression to confer multidrug resistance.
ANT(3'')-IIa is a aminoglycoside nucleotidyltransferase identified in Acinetobacter spp. via horizontal gene transfer mechanisms.

SAT-2 is a plasmid-mediated streptothricin acetyltransferase which confers resistance to streptothricin a nucleoside antibiotic. Originally described from an E. coli plasmid sequence by Heim et al. 1989.
dfrA1 is an integron-encoded dihydrofolate reductase
A class C ampC beta-lactamase (cephalosporinase) enzyme described in Escherichia coli shown clinically to confer resistance to penicillin-like and cephalosporin-class antibiotics.

PmrE is required for the synthesis and transfer of 4-amino-4-deoxy-L-arabinose (Ara4N) to Lipid A which allows gram-negative bacteria to resist the antimicrobial activity of cationic antimicrobial peptides and antibiotics such as polymyxin
CRP is a global regulator that represses MdtEF multidrug efflux pump expression.
TetA is a tetracycline efflux pump found in many species of Gram-negative bacteria.

Member of the small MDR (multidrug resistance) family of transporters; in Escherichia coli this protein provides resistance against a number of positively charged compounds including ethidium bromide and erythromycin; proton-dependent secondary transporter which exchanges protons for compound translocation
MdtA is the membrane fusion protein of the multidrug efflux complex mdtABC.
MdtB is a transporter that forms a heteromultimer complex with MdtC to form a multidrug transporter. MdtBC is part of the MdtABC-TolC efflux complex.

MdtC is a transporter that forms a heteromultimer complex with MdtB to form a multidrug transporter. MdtBC is part of the MdtABC-TolC efflux complex. In the absence of MdtB MdtC can form a homomultimer complex that results in a functioning efflux complex with a narrower drug specificity. mdtC corresponds to 3 loci in Pseudomonas aeruginosa PAO1 (gene name: muxC/muxB) and 3 loci in Pseudomonas aeruginosa LESB58.
BaeS is a sensor kinase in the BaeSR regulatory system. While it phosphorylates BaeR to increase its activity BaeS is not necessary for overexpressed BaeR to confer resistance.
BaeR is a response regulator that promotes the expression of MdtABC and AcrD efflux complexes.
The bacA gene product (BacA) recycles undecaprenyl pyrophosphate during cell wall biosynthesis which confers resistance to bacitracin.

TolC is a protein subunit of many multidrug efflux complexes in Gram negative bacteria. It is an outer membrane efflux protein and is constitutively open. Regulation of efflux activity is often at its periplasmic entrance by other components of the efflux complex.
Tet(B) is a tetracycline efflux protein expressed in many Gram-negative bacteria. It confers resistance to tetracycline doxycycline and minocycline but not tigecycline.

AAC(6')-Ib-cr is an aminoglycoside acetyltransferase encoded by plasmids transposons integrons in Enterobacteriaceae. The aac(6')-Ib-cr variant gene can induce resistance against aminoglycoside and fluoroquinolone simultaneously
OXA-1 is a beta-lactamase found in E. coli
AmpH is a class C ampC-like beta-lactamase and penicillin-binding protein identified in Escherichia coli.

Protein subunit of AcrA-AcrB-TolC multidrug efflux complex. AcrB functions as a herterotrimer which forms the inner membrane component and is primarily responsible for substrate recognition and energy transduction by acting as a drug/proton antiporter.
AcrA is a subunit of the AcrAB-TolC multidrug efflux system that in E. coli.
Multidrug efflux pump in E. coli. This multidrug efflux system was originally identified as the Cmr/CmlA chloramphenicol exporter.
AcrS is a repressor of the AcrAB efflux complex and is associated with the expression of AcrEF. AcrS is believed to regulate a switch between AcrAB and AcrEF efflux.
AcrE is a membrane fusion protein similar to AcrA.
AcrF is a inner membrane transporter similar to AcrB.

H-NS is a histone-like protein involved in global gene regulation in Gram-negative bacteria. It is a repressor of the membrane fusion protein genes acrE mdtE and emrK as well as nearby genes of many RND-type multidrug exporters.

MsbA is a member of the MDR-ABC transporter group by sequence homology. MsbA transports lipid A a major component of the bacterial outer cell membrane and is the only bacterial ABC transporter that is essential for cell viability.

emrB is a translocase in the emrB -TolC efflux protein in E. coli. It recognizes substrates including carbonyl cyanide m-chlorophenylhydrazone (CCCP) nalidixic acid and thioloactomycin.
In the presence of antibiotic stress E. coli overexpresses the global activator protein MarA which besides inducing MDR efflux pump AcrAB also down- regulates synthesis of the porin OmpF.

PmrE is required for the synthesis and transfer of 4-amino-4-deoxy-L-arabinose (Ara4N) to Lipid A which allows gram-negative bacteria to resist the antimicrobial activity of cationic antimicrobial peptides and antibiotics such as polymyxin
CpxA is a membrane-localized sensor kinase that is activated by envelope stress. It starts a kinase cascade that activates CpxR which promotes efflux complex expression.
emrY is a multidrug transport that moves substrates across the inner membrane of the Gram-negative E. coli. It is a homolog of emrB.
emrK is a membrane fusion protein that is a homolog of EmrA. Together with the inner membrane transporter EmrY and the outer membrane channel TolC it mediates multidrug efflux.

EvgA when phosphorylated is a positive regulator for efflux protein complexes emrKY and mdtEF. While usually phosphorylated in a EvgS dependent manner it can be phosphorylated in the absence of EvgS when overexpressed.
EvgS is a sensor protein that phosphorylates the regulatory protein EvgA. evgS corresponds to 1 locus in Pseudomonas aeruginosa PAO1 and 1 locus in Pseudomonas aeruginosa LESB58.
AmpH is a class C ampC-like beta-lactamase and penicillin-binding protein identified in Escherichia coli.

Protein subunit of AcrA-AcrB-TolC multidrug efflux complex. AcrB functions as a herterotrimer which forms the inner membrane component and is primarily responsible for substrate recognition and energy transduction by acting as a drug/proton antiporter.
AcrA is a subunit of the AcrAB-TolC multidrug efflux system that in E. coli.

AcrD is an aminoglycoside efflux pump expressed in E. coli. Its expression can be induced by indole and is regulated by baeRS and cpxAR.
Multidrug resistance efflux pump. Could be involved in resistance to puromycin acriflavine and tetraphenylarsonium chloride
Multidrug resistance efflux pump. Could be involved in resistance to puromycin acriflavine and tetraphenylarsonium chloride

PmrC mediates the modification of Lipid A by the addition of 4-amino-4-deoxy-L-arabinose (L-Ara4N) and phosphoethanolamine resulting in a less negative cell membrane and decreased binding of polymyxin B.

BaeS is a sensor kinase in the BaeSR regulatory system. While it phosphorylates BaeR to increase its activity BaeS is not necessary for overexpressed BaeR to confer resistance.

MdtC is a transporter that forms a heteromultimer complex with MdtB to form a multidrug transporter. MdtBC is part of the MdtABC-TolC efflux complex. MdtB is a transporter that forms a heteromultimer complex with MdtC to form a multidrug transporter. MdtBC is part of the MdtABC-TolC efflux complex.

PmrF is required for the synthesis and transfer of 4-amino-4-deoxy-L-arabinose (Ara4N) to Lipid A which allows gram-negative bacteria to resist the antimicrobial activity of cationic antimicrobial peptides and antibiotics such as polymyxin. pmrF corresponds to 1 locus in Pseudomonas aeruginosa PAO1 and 1 locus in Pseudomonas aeruginosa LESB58.
A class C ampC beta-lactamase (cephalosporinase) enzyme described in Escherichia coli shown clinically to confer resistance to penicillin-like and cephalosporin-class antibiotics.

kdpE is a transcriptional activator that is part of the two-component system KdpD/KdpE that is studied for its regulatory role in potassium transport and has been identified as an adaptive regulator involved in the virulence and intracellular survival of pathogenic bacteria. kdpE regulates a range of virulence loci through direct promoter binding.

TolC is a protein subunit of many multidrug efflux complexes in Gram negative bacteria. It is an outer membrane efflux protein and is constitutively open. Regulation of efflux activity is often at its periplasmic entrance by other components of the efflux complex.
The bacA gene product (BacA) recycles undecaprenyl pyrophosphate during cell wall biosynthesis which confers resistance to bacitracin.
CTX-M-15 is a beta-lactamase found in the Enterobacteriaceae family

MdtF is the multidrug inner membrane transporter for the MdtEF-TolC efflux complex.
MdtE is the membrane fusion protein of the MdtEF multidrug efflux complex. It shares 70% sequence similarity with AcrA.

AAC(3)-IIe is a plasmid-encoded aminoglycoside acetyltransferase in E. coli

smeD is the membrane fusion protein of the smeDEF multidrug efflux complex in Stenotrophomonas maltophilia
smeE is the RND protein of the efflux complex smeDEF in Stenotrophomonas maltophilia
smeF is an outer membrane multidrug efflux protein of the smeDEF complex in Stenotrophomonas maltophilia

L1 is an Ambler class B MBL; subclass B3 originally isolated from Stenotrophomonas maltophilia.  It has activity against a broad range of beta-lactams and is only active with two Zn(II) ions in the active site.
smeR is the responder component of a two component signal transduction system that includes smeS
smeS is the protein kinase sensor component of a two component signal transduction system that includes smeR
smeA is the membrane fusion protein of the smeABC multidrug efflux complex in Stenotrophomonas maltophilia
smeB is the inner membrane multidrug exporter of the efflux complex smeABC in Stenotrophomonas maltophilia
smeC is an outer membrane multidrug efflux protein of the smeABC complex in Stenotrophomonas maltophilia
APH(3')-IIc is a chromosomal-encoded aminoglycoside phosphotransferase in S. maltophilia

AdeH is the outer membrane channel protein of the AdeFGH multidrug efflux complex.
AdeF is the membrane fusion protein of the multidrug efflux complex AdeFGH.
AdeG is the inner membrane transporter of the AdeFGH multidrug efflux complex.
AdeL is a regulator of AdeFGH in Acinetobacter baumannii. AdeL mutations are associated with AdeFGH overexpression and multidrug resistance.
AbeS in an efflux pump of the SMR family of transporters found in Acinetobacter baumannii.
AdeK is the outer membrane factor protein in the adeIJK multidrug efflux complex.
AdeJ is a RND efflux protein that acts as the inner membrane transporter of the AdeIJK efflux complex. It has 57% identity with E. coli AcrB.
AdeI is the membrane fusion protein of the AdeIJK multidrug efflux complex.
ADC-22 is a beta-lactamase found in Acinetobacter pittii.

AmvA has 14 alpha-helical transmembrane segments qualifying it as a member of the DHA2 transporter family of the major facilitator superfamily (MFS). When AmvA was expressed in E. coli  the cells had at least four-fold decreased susceptibility to erythromycin acridine orange acriflavine deoxycholate and methyl viologen. AmvA from the AC0037 strain of A. baumannii was tested.
AbaQ is an MFS transporter mainly involved in the extrusion of quinolone-type drugs in A. baumannii
From the Lahey list of beta-lactamases. Not yet released.

Klebsiella pneumoniae outer membrane porin protein. Is preferentially detected in porin-deficient strains. Functional characterization of this new porin revealed a narrower pore than those of porins OmpK35 and OmpK36 which did not allow penetration by certain beta-lactams. Also when a resistant strain expresses porin OmpK37 is less susceptible to cefotaxime and cefoxitin than when it is expressing either OmpK36 or OmpK35.
AcrD is an aminoglycoside efflux pump expressed in E. coli. Its expression can be induced by indole and is regulated by baeRS and cpxAR.
MdtB is a transporter that forms a heteromultimer complex with MdtC to form a multidrug transporter. MdtBC is part of the MdtABC-TolC efflux complex.

MdtC is a transporter that forms a heteromultimer complex with MdtB to form a multidrug transporter. MdtBC is part of the MdtABC-TolC efflux complex. In the absence of MdtB MdtC can form a homomultimer complex that results in a functioning efflux complex with a narrower drug specificity. mdtC corresponds to 3 loci in Pseudomonas aeruginosa PAO1 (gene name: muxC/muxB) and 3 loci in Pseudomonas aeruginosa LESB58.
BaeR is a response regulator that promotes the expression of MdtABC and AcrD efflux complexes.

KpnF subunit of KpnEF resembles EbrAB from E. coli. Mutation in KpnEF resulted in increased susceptibility to cefepime ceftriaxon colistin erythromycin rifampin tetracycline and streptomycin as well as enhanced sensitivity toward sodium dodecyl sulfate deoxycholate dyes benzalkonium chloride chlorhexidine and triclosan.

KpnE subunit of KpnEF resembles EbrAB from E. coli. Mutation in KpnEF resulted in increased susceptibility to cefepime ceftriaxon colistin erythromycin rifampin tetracycline and streptomycin as well as enhanced sensitivity toward sodium dodecyl sulfate deoxycholate dyes benzalkonium chloride chlorhexidine and triclosan
CpxA is a membrane-localized sensor kinase that is activated by envelope stress. It starts a kinase cascade that activates CpxR which promotes efflux complex expression.

RamA (resistance antibiotic multiple) is a positive regulator of AcrAB-TolC and leads to high level multidrug resistance in Klebsiella pneumoniae Salmonella enterica and Enterobacter aerugenes increasing the expression of both the mar operon as well as AcrAB. RamA also decreases OmpF expression.

H-NS is a histone-like protein involved in global gene regulation in Gram-negative bacteria. It is a repressor of the membrane fusion protein genes acrE mdtE and emrK as well as nearby genes of many RND-type multidrug exporters.
In the presence of antibiotic stress E. coli overexpresses the global activator protein MarA which besides inducing MDR efflux pump AcrAB also down- regulates synthesis of the porin OmpF.

fosA5 is a fosfomycin resistance gene isolated from clinical strain of Escherichia coli E265. It is susceptible to amikacin tetracycline and imipenem and resistant to sulphonamide cephalosporins gentamicin ciprofloxacin chloramphenicol and streptomycin
The bacA gene product (BacA) recycles undecaprenyl pyrophosphate during cell wall biosynthesis which confers resistance to bacitracin.
AcrA is a subunit of the AcrAB multidrug efflux system that in K. pneumoniae which is encoded by the acrRAB operon.

RND efflux pump conferring resistance to fluoroquinolone
EmrR is a negative regulator for the EmrAB-TolC multidrug efflux pump in E. coli. Mutations lead to EmrAB-TolC overexpression.

KpnG consists of ~390 residues and resembles EmrA of E. coli. Disruption of the pump components KpnG-KpnH signficantly decrease resistance to azithromycin ceftazidime ciprofloxacin ertapenem erythromycin gentamicin imipenem ticarcillin norfloxacin polymyxin-B piperacillin spectinomycin tobramycin and streptomycin

KpnH consists of ~511 residues resembles EmrB of E. coli and is probably a translocase in the KpnGH-TolC efflux protein in K. pneumoniae. Disruption of the pump components KpnG-KpnH signficantly decrease resistance to azithromycin ceftazidime ciprofloxacin ertapenem erythromycin gentamicin imipenem ticarcillin norfloxacin polymyxin-B piperacillin spectinomycin tobramycin and streptomycin.
dfrC is a chromosome-encoded dihydrofolate reductase found in Staphylococcus aureus

Mel a homolog of MsrA is an ABC-F subfamily protein associated with macrolide resistance. It is expressed on the same operon as mefA and mefE both MFS-type efflux proteins that confer macrolide resistance.
The blaZ beta-lactamase is found in Bacillus subtilis and Staphylococcus aureus.
A foreign PBP2a acquired by lateral gene transfer that able to perform peptidoglycan synthesis in the presence of beta-lactams.
The blaZ beta-lactamase is found in Bacillus subtilis and Staphylococcus aureus.
qacA is a subunit of the qac multidrug efflux pump
Kanamycin nucleotidyltransferase sequence from Staphylococcus aureus plasmid. Confers resistance to kanamycin neomycin and other aminoglycosides

NorA is a multidrug efflux pump in Staphylococcus aureus that confers resistance to fluoroquinolones and other structurally unrelated antibiotics like acriflavine. It shares 30% similarity with NorA and is a structural homolog of Bmr of Bacillus subtilis. It is regulated by arlRS and mgrA the latter also known as NorR.
MgrA also known as NorR is a regulator for norA norB and tet38. It is a positive regulator for norA expression but is a direct repressor for norB and an indirect repressor of tet38.
APH(3')-IIIa is a plasmid-encoded aminoglycoside phosphotransferase in S. aureus and Enterococcus spp.

SAT-4 is a plasmid-mediated streptothricin acetyltransferase and streptothricin (a nucleoside antibiotic) resistant determinant. Originally described from a Campylobacter coli BE/G4 plasmid gene sequence by Jacob et al 1994.
AAC(6')-Ie-APH(2'')-Ia is an aminoglycoside acetyltransferase encoded by plasmids and transposons in S. aureus E. faecalis E. faecium and Staphylococcus warneri

PmpM is a multidrug efflux pump belonging to the MATE family of Pseudomonas aeruginosa. PmpM is an H+ drug antiporter and is the first reported case of an H+ coupled efflux pump in the MATE family. PmpM confers resistance to fluoroquinolones fradiomycin benzalkonium chloride chlorhexidine gluconate ethidium bromide tetraphenylphosphonium chloride (TPPCl) and rhodamine 6G.

CpxR is directly involved in activation of expression of RND efflux pump MexAB-OprM in P. aeruginosa. CpxR is required to enhance mexAB-oprM expression and drug resistance in the absence of repressor MexR.
TriA is a membrane protein that is fused to TriB and both are required for the triclosan efflux pump function of TriABC-OpmH in P. aeruginosa.
TriB is a membrane protein that is fused to TriA and both are required for the triclosan efflux pump function of TriABC-OpmH in P. aeruginosa.
TriC is a resistance nodulation cell division (RND) transporter that is a part of TriABC-OpmH a triclosan-specific efflux protein.
catB7 is a chromosome-encoded variant of the cat gene found in Pseudomonas aeruginosa
MexP is the membrane fusion protein of the MexPQ-OpmE multidrug efflux complex
MexQ is the inner membrane transporter of the multidrug efflux pump MexPQ-OpmE.
opmE is an outer membrane factor protein that is part of the multidrug efflux pump MexPQ-OpmE.
MexN is the inner membrane transporter of the MexMN-OprM multidrug efflux complex.
mexM is the membrane fusion protein of the MexMN-OprM multidrug efflux complex.

ArmR a 53-amino-acid antirepressor allosterically inhibits MexR dimer-DNA binding by occupying a hydrophobic binding cavity within the center of the MexR dimer. ArmR up-regulation and MexR-ArmR complex formation have previously been shown to upregulate MexAB-OprM.
MexL is a specific repressor of mexJK transcription and autoregulates its own expression.
mexJ is the membrane fusion protein of the MexJK multidrug efflux protein.
mexK is the inner membrane resistance-nodulation-cell division (RND) transporter in the MexJK multidrug efflux protein.

arnA modifies lipid A with 4-amino-4-deoxy-L-arabinose (Ara4N) which allows gram-negative bacteria to resist the antimicrobial activity of cationic antimicrobial peptides and antibiotics such as polymyxin. arnA is found in E. coli and P. aeruginosa.

An enzyme that confers resistance to fosfomycin in Serratia marcescens by breaking the epoxide ring of the molecule. It depends on the cofactors Manganese (II) and Potassium and uses Glutathione (GSH) as the nucleophilic molecule. In Pseudomonas aeruginosa FosA catalyzes the conjugation of glutathione to carbon-1 of fosfomycin rendering it ineffective as an antibacterial drug.
PDC-3 is a extended-spectrum beta-lactamase found in Pseudomonas aeruginosa.
APH(3')-IIb is a chromosomal-encoded aminoglycoside phosphotransferase in P. aeruginosa

Transmembrane protein which expels bicyclomycin from the cell leading to bicyclomycin resistance. Identified in Pseudomonas aeruginosa strains responsible for outbreaks in Brazil often appearing with blaSPM-1 another bicyclomycin resistance gene

MexH is the membrane fusion protein of the efflux complex MexGHI-OpmD.
MexI is the inner membrane transporter of the efflux complex MexGHI-OpmD.
OpmD is the outer membrane channel protein of the efflux complex MexGHI-OpmD.

MexB is the inner membrane multidrug exporter of the efflux complex MexAB-OprM.
MexA is the membrane fusion protein of the MexAB-OprM multidrug efflux complex.

PmrC mediates the modification of Lipid A by the addition of 4-amino-4-deoxy-L-arabinose (L-Ara4N) and phosphoethanolamine resulting in a less negative cell membrane and decreased binding of polymyxin B.
CpxA is a membrane-localized sensor kinase that is activated by envelope stress. It starts a kinase cascade that activates CpxR which promotes efflux complex expression.

kdpE is a transcriptional activator that is part of the two-component system KdpD/KdpE that is studied for its regulatory role in potassium transport and has been identified as an adaptive regulator involved in the virulence and intracellular survival of pathogenic bacteria. kdpE regulates a range of virulence loci through direct promoter binding.
Multidrug resistance protein MdtH

The MdtG protein also named YceE appears to be a member of the major facilitator superfamily of transporters and it has been reported when overexpressed to increase fosfomycin and deoxycholate resistances. mdtG is a member of the marA-soxS-rob regulon.

MsbA is a multidrug resistance transporter homolog from E. coli and belongs to a superfamily of transporters that contain an adenosine triphosphate (ATP) binding cassette (ABC) which is also called a nucleotide-binding domain (NBD). MsbA is a member of the MDR-ABC transporter group by sequence homology. MsbA transports lipid A a major component of the bacterial outer cell membrane and is the only bacterial ABC transporter that is essential for cell viability.
Multidrug efflux pump in E. coli. This multidrug efflux system was originally identified as the Cmr/CmlA chloramphenicol exporter.

H-NS is a histone-like protein involved in global gene regulation in Gram-negative bacteria. It is a repressor of the membrane fusion protein genes acrE mdtE and emrK as well as nearby genes of many RND-type multidrug exporters.
Multidrug resistance protein MdtM

PmrF is required for the synthesis and transfer of 4-amino-4-deoxy-L-arabinose (Ara4N) to Lipid A which allows gram-negative bacteria to resist the antimicrobial activity of cationic antimicrobial peptides and antibiotics such as polymyxin. pmrF corresponds to 1 locus in Pseudomonas aeruginosa PAO1 and 1 locus in Pseudomonas aeruginosa LESB58.

YojI mediates resistance to the peptide antibiotic microcin J25 when it is expressed from a multicopy vector. YojI is capable of pumping out microcin molecules.  The outer membrane protein TolC in addition to YojI is required for export of microcin J25 out of the cell. Microcin J25 is thus the first known substrate for YojI.
BaeR is a response regulator that promotes the expression of MdtABC and AcrD efflux complexes.
BaeS is a sensor kinase in the BaeSR regulatory system. While it phosphorylates BaeR to increase its activity BaeS is not necessary for overexpressed BaeR to confer resistance.

MdtC is a transporter that forms a heteromultimer complex with MdtB to form a multidrug transporter. MdtBC is part of the MdtABC-TolC efflux complex. In the absence of MdtB MdtC can form a homomultimer complex that results in a functioning efflux complex with a narrower drug specificity. mdtC corresponds to 3 loci in Pseudomonas aeruginosa PAO1 (gene name: muxC/muxB) and 3 loci in Pseudomonas aeruginosa LESB58.
MdtB is a transporter that forms a heteromultimer complex with MdtC to form a multidrug transporter. MdtBC is part of the MdtABC-TolC efflux complex.
MdtA is the membrane fusion protein of the multidrug efflux complex mdtABC.

PmrE is required for the synthesis and transfer of 4-amino-4-deoxy-L-arabinose (Ara4N) to Lipid A which allows gram-negative bacteria to resist the antimicrobial activity of cationic antimicrobial peptides and antibiotics such as polymyxin

Member of the small MDR (multidrug resistance) family of transporters; in Escherichia coli this protein provides resistance against a number of positively charged compounds including ethidium bromide and erythromycin; proton-dependent secondary transporter which exchanges protons for compound translocation

EvgA when phosphorylated is a positive regulator for efflux protein complexes emrKY and mdtEF. While usually phosphorylated in a EvgS dependent manner it can be phosphorylated in the absence of EvgS when overexpressed.
EvgS is a sensor protein that phosphorylates the regulatory protein EvgA. evgS corresponds to 1 locus in Pseudomonas aeruginosa PAO1 and 1 locus in Pseudomonas aeruginosa LESB58.
EmrR is a negative regulator for the EmrAB-TolC multidrug efflux pump in E. coli. Mutations lead to EmrAB-TolC overexpression.
EmrA is a membrane fusion protein providing an efflux pathway with EmrB and TolC between the inner and outer membranes of E. coli a Gram-negative bacterium.
emrB is a translocase in the emrB -TolC efflux protein in E. coli. It recognizes substrates including carbonyl cyanide m-chlorophenylhydrazone (CCCP) nalidixic acid and thioloactomycin.
In the presence of antibiotic stress E. coli overexpresses the global activator protein MarA which besides inducing MDR efflux pump AcrAB also down- regulates synthesis of the porin OmpF.
A class C ampC beta-lactamase (cephalosporinase) enzyme described in Escherichia coli shown clinically to confer resistance to penicillin-like and cephalosporin-class antibiotics.
AmpH is a class C ampC-like beta-lactamase and penicillin-binding protein identified in Escherichia coli.

Protein subunit of AcrA-AcrB-TolC multidrug efflux complex. AcrB functions as a herterotrimer which forms the inner membrane component and is primarily responsible for substrate recognition and energy transduction by acting as a drug/proton antiporter.
AcrA is a subunit of the AcrAB-TolC multidrug efflux system that in E. coli.
dfrA17 is an integron-encoded dihydrofolate reductase found in Escherichia coli
aadA5 is an aminoglycoside nucleotidyltransferase gene encoded by plasmids transposons and integrons in E. coli K. pneumoniae Kluyvera georgiana P. aeruginosa and E. cloacae
Sul1 is a sulfonamide resistant dihydropteroate synthase of Gram-negative bacteria. It is linked to other resistance genes of class 1 integrons.

The mphA gene encodes for resistance enzyme MPH(2')-I which preferentially inactivate 14-membered macrolides (e.g.erythromycin telithromycin roxithromycin) over 16-membered macrolides (e.g.tylosin spiramycin). It phosphorylates macrolides at 2'-OH hydroxyl of desosamine sugar of macrolides in a GTP-dependent manner.
An ampC-like beta-lactamase identified from Escherichia coli.
AcrD is an aminoglycoside efflux pump expressed in E. coli. Its expression can be induced by indole and is regulated by baeRS and cpxAR.

The mphB gene encodes for MPH(2')-II. This enzymes phosphorylates 14-membered and 16-membered macrolides.  It phosphorylates macrolides in GTP- dependent manner at 2'-OH hydroxyl of desosamine sugar of macrolides.
CRP is a global regulator that represses MdtEF multidrug efflux pump expression.
MdtE is the membrane fusion protein of the MdtEF multidrug efflux complex. It shares 70% sequence similarity with AcrA.
MdtF is the multidrug inner membrane transporter for the MdtEF-TolC efflux complex.

GadW is an AraC-family regulator that promotes mdtEF expression to confer multidrug resistance. GadW inhibits GadX-dependent activation. GadW clearly represses gadX and in situations where GadX is missing activates gadA and gadBC.
GadX is an AraC-family regulator that promotes mdtEF expression to confer multidrug resistance.
emrK is a membrane fusion protein that is a homolog of EmrA. Together with the inner membrane transporter EmrY and the outer membrane channel TolC it mediates multidrug efflux.
emrY is a multidrug transport that moves substrates across the inner membrane of the Gram-negative E. coli. It is a homolog of emrB.
catB3 is a plasmid or chromosome-encoded variant of the cat gene found in Salmonella typhimurium Acinetobacter baumannii and Escherichia coli
OXA-1 is a beta-lactamase found in E. coli

AAC(6')-Ib-cr is an aminoglycoside acetyltransferase encoded by plasmids transposons integrons in Enterobacteriaceae. The aac(6')-Ib-cr variant gene can induce resistance against aminoglycoside and fluoroquinolone simultaneously
The bacA gene product (BacA) recycles undecaprenyl pyrophosphate during cell wall biosynthesis which confers resistance to bacitracin.

TolC is a protein subunit of many multidrug efflux complexes in Gram negative bacteria. It is an outer membrane efflux protein and is constitutively open. Regulation of efflux activity is often at its periplasmic entrance by other components of the efflux complex.
MexW is the RND-type membrane protein of the efflux complex MexVW-OprM.
MexV is the membrane fusion protein of the MexVW-OprM multidrug efflux complex.
TriC is a resistance nodulation cell division (RND) transporter that is a part of TriABC-OpmH a triclosan-specific efflux protein.
TriB is a membrane protein that is fused to TriA and both are required for the triclosan efflux pump function of TriABC-OpmH in P. aeruginosa.
TriA is a membrane protein that is fused to TriB and both are required for the triclosan efflux pump function of TriABC-OpmH in P. aeruginosa.
PDC-1 is a beta-lactamase found in Pseudomonas aeruginosa.
APH(3')-IIb is a chromosomal-encoded aminoglycoside phosphotransferase in P. aeruginosa

Transmembrane protein which expels bicyclomycin from the cell leading to bicyclomycin resistance. Identified in Pseudomonas aeruginosa strains responsible for outbreaks in Brazil often appearing with blaSPM-1 another bicyclomycin resistance gene

CpxR is directly involved in activation of expression of RND efflux pump MexAB-OprM in P. aeruginosa. CpxR is required to enhance mexAB-oprM expression and drug resistance in the absence of repressor MexR.
MexC is the membrane fusion protein of the MexCD-OprJ multidrug efflux complex.
MexD is the multidrug inner membrane transporter of the MexCD-OprJ complex.
OprJ is the outer membrane channel component of the MexCD-OprJ multidrug efflux complex.

arnA modifies lipid A with 4-amino-4-deoxy-L-arabinose (Ara4N) which allows gram-negative bacteria to resist the antimicrobial activity of cationic antimicrobial peptides and antibiotics such as polymyxin. arnA is found in E. coli and P. aeruginosa.
MexP is the membrane fusion protein of the MexPQ-OpmE multidrug efflux complex
MexQ is the inner membrane transporter of the multidrug efflux pump MexPQ-OpmE.
opmE is an outer membrane factor protein that is part of the multidrug efflux pump MexPQ-OpmE.

An enzyme that confers resistance to fosfomycin in Serratia marcescens by breaking the epoxide ring of the molecule. It depends on the cofactors Manganese (II) and Potassium and uses Glutathione (GSH) as the nucleophilic molecule. In Pseudomonas aeruginosa FosA catalyzes the conjugation of glutathione to carbon-1 of fosfomycin rendering it ineffective as an antibacterial drug.

PmpM is a multidrug efflux pump belonging to the MATE family of Pseudomonas aeruginosa. PmpM is an H+ drug antiporter and is the first reported case of an H+ coupled efflux pump in the MATE family. PmpM confers resistance to fluoroquinolones fradiomycin benzalkonium chloride chlorhexidine gluconate ethidium bromide tetraphenylphosphonium chloride (TPPCl) and rhodamine 6G.
mexM is the membrane fusion protein of the MexMN-OprM multidrug efflux complex.
MexN is the inner membrane transporter of the MexMN-OprM multidrug efflux complex.
MexG is a membrane protein required for MexGHI-OpmD efflux activity.
MexH is the membrane fusion protein of the efflux complex MexGHI-OpmD.
MexI is the inner membrane transporter of the efflux complex MexGHI-OpmD.
OpmD is the outer membrane channel protein of the efflux complex MexGHI-OpmD.
catB7 is a chromosome-encoded variant of the cat gene found in Pseudomonas aeruginosa
Histidine protein kinase sensor Lipid A modification gene; part of a two-component system involved in polymyxin resistance that senses high extracellular Fe(2+)
OpmH is an outer membrane efflux protein required for triclosan-specific efflux pump function.

EmrE is a small multidrug transporter that functions as a homodimer and that couples the efflux of small polyaromatic cations from the cell with the import of protons down an electrochemical gradient. Confers resistance to tetraphenylphosphonium methyl viologen gentamicin kanamycin and neomycin.
MexY is the RND-type membrane protein of the efflux complex MexXY-OprM.
MexX is the membrane fusion protein of the MexXY-OprM multidrug efflux complex.
MexA is the membrane fusion protein of the MexAB-OprM multidrug efflux complex.
MexB is the inner membrane multidrug exporter of the efflux complex MexAB-OprM.
OprM is an outer membrane factor protein found in Pseudomonas aeruginosa and Burkholderia vietnamiensis. It is part of the MexAB-OprM MexVW-OprM MexXY-OprM and the AmrAB-OprM complex.

ArmR a 53-amino-acid antirepressor allosterically inhibits MexR dimer-DNA binding by occupying a hydrophobic binding cavity within the center of the MexR dimer. ArmR up-regulation and MexR-ArmR complex formation have previously been shown to upregulate MexAB-OprM.
MexL is a specific repressor of mexJK transcription and autoregulates its own expression.
mexJ is the membrane fusion protein of the MexJK multidrug efflux protein.
mexK is the inner membrane resistance-nodulation-cell division (RND) transporter in the MexJK multidrug efflux protein.
Assigned by Lahey's list of beta-lactamases no accessions or other information available

SoxR is a redox-sensitive transcriptional activator that induces expression of a small regulon that includes the RND efflux pump-encoding operon mexGHI-opmD. SoxR was shown to be activated by pyocyanin.
MexE is the membrane fusion protein of the MexEF-OprN multidrug efflux complex.

MexF is the multidrug inner membrane transporter of the MexEF-OprN complex. mexF corresponds to 2 loci in Pseudomonas aeruginosa PAO1 (gene name: mexF/mexB) and 4 loci in Pseudomonas aeruginosa LESB58 (gene name: mexD/mexB).
OprN is the outer membrane channel component of the MexEF-OprN multidrug efflux complex.
OpmB is an outer membrane efflux protein in Pseudomonas aeruginosa that shows functional cooperation with MuxABC to form the efflux pump system MuxABC-OpmB.
MuxC is one of the two necessary RND components of the MuxABC-OpmB efflux pumps system in Pseudomonas aeruginosa.
MuxB is one of the two necessary RND components in the Pseudomonas aeruginosa efflux pump system MuxABC-OpmB.
MuxA is a membrane fusion protein component of the efflux pump system MuxABC-OpmB in Pseudomonas aeruginosa.
In the presence of antibiotic stress E. coli overexpresses the global activator protein MarA which besides inducing MDR efflux pump AcrAB also down- regulates synthesis of the porin OmpF.
CRP is a global regulator that represses MdtEF multidrug efflux pump expression.
The bacA gene product (BacA) recycles undecaprenyl pyrophosphate during cell wall biosynthesis which confers resistance to bacitracin.

TolC is a protein subunit of many multidrug efflux complexes in Gram negative bacteria. It is an outer membrane efflux protein and is constitutively open. Regulation of efflux activity is often at its periplasmic entrance by other components of the efflux complex.

RamA (resistance antibiotic multiple) is a positive regulator of AcrAB-TolC and leads to high level multidrug resistance in Klebsiella pneumoniae Salmonella enterica and Enterobacter aerugenes increasing the expression of both the mar operon as well as AcrAB. RamA also decreases OmpF expression.
emrB is a translocase in the emrB -TolC efflux protein in E. coli. It recognizes substrates including carbonyl cyanide m-chlorophenylhydrazone (CCCP) nalidixic acid and thioloactomycin.

KpnG consists of ~390 residues and resembles EmrA of E. coli. Disruption of the pump components KpnG-KpnH signficantly decrease resistance to azithromycin ceftazidime ciprofloxacin ertapenem erythromycin gentamicin imipenem ticarcillin norfloxacin polymyxin-B piperacillin spectinomycin tobramycin and streptomycin
EmrR is a negative regulator for the EmrAB-TolC multidrug efflux pump in E. coli. Mutations lead to EmrAB-TolC overexpression.

MsbA is a multidrug resistance transporter homolog from E. coli and belongs to a superfamily of transporters that contain an adenosine triphosphate (ATP) binding cassette (ABC) which is also called a nucleotide-binding domain (NBD). MsbA is a member of the MDR-ABC transporter group by sequence homology. MsbA transports lipid A a major component of the bacterial outer cell membrane and is the only bacterial ABC transporter that is essential for cell viability.
CpxA is a membrane-localized sensor kinase that is activated by envelope stress. It starts a kinase cascade that activates CpxR which promotes efflux complex expression.
MIR-5 is a beta-lactamase. From the Lahey list of MIR beta-lactamases.
RND efflux pump conferring resistance to fluoroquinolone
RND efflux pump conferring resistance to fluoroquinolone
BaeR is a response regulator that promotes the expression of MdtABC and AcrD efflux complexes.

MdtC is a transporter that forms a heteromultimer complex with MdtB to form a multidrug transporter. MdtBC is part of the MdtABC-TolC efflux complex. In the absence of MdtB MdtC can form a homomultimer complex that results in a functioning efflux complex with a narrower drug specificity. mdtC corresponds to 3 loci in Pseudomonas aeruginosa PAO1 (gene name: muxC/muxB) and 3 loci in Pseudomonas aeruginosa LESB58.
MdtB is a transporter that forms a heteromultimer complex with MdtC to form a multidrug transporter. MdtBC is part of the MdtABC-TolC efflux complex.

An enzyme that confers resistance to fosfomycin in Enterobacter cloacae by breaking the epoxide ring of the molecule. It depends on the cofactors Manganese (II) and Potassium and uses Glutathione (GSH) as the nucleophilic molecule.
AcrA is a subunit of the AcrAB-TolC multidrug efflux system that in E. cloacae.

Protein subunit of AcrA-AcrB-TolC multidrug efflux complex. AcrB functions as a herterotrimer which forms the inner membrane component and is primarily responsible for substrate recognition and energy transduction by acting as a drug/proton antiporter.
AcrD is an aminoglycoside efflux pump expressed in E. coli. Its expression can be induced by indole and is regulated by baeRS and cpxAR.

H-NS is a histone-like protein involved in global gene regulation in Gram-negative bacteria. It is a repressor of the membrane fusion protein genes acrE mdtE and emrK as well as nearby genes of many RND-type multidrug exporters.
